title: Document AI - Method: processorVersions.delete
abstract:
# Document AI - Method: processorVersions.delete
**Full name** : projects.locations.processors.processorVersions.delete
Deletes the processor version, all artifacts under the processor version will be deleted.
#
content:
## HTTP request`DELETE https://{endpoint}/v1beta3/{name}`
Where `{endpoint}` is one of the [supported service endpoints](/document-ai/docs/reference/rest#rest_endpoints) .
### Path parameters| Parameters | Parameters.1                                                                          |
|:-------------|:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| name   | string Required. The processor version resource name to be deleted. It takes the form projects/{project}/locations/{location}/processors/{processor}/processorVersions/{processorversion}. Authorization requires the following IAM permission on the specified resource name: documentai.processorVersions.delete |
### Request bodyThe request body must be empty.
### Response bodyIf successful, the response body contains an instance of ` [Operation](/document-ai/docs/reference/rest/Shared.Types/ListOperationsResponse#Operation) ` .
### Authorization scopesRequires the following OAuth scope:- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform`For more information, see the [Authentication Overview](https://cloud.google.com/docs/authentication/) .
### IAM PermissionsRequires the following [IAM](https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs) permission on the `name` resource:- `documentai.processorVersions.delete`For more information, see the [IAM documentation](https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs) .
